review_blob: Sorry I just did not like this beer. The oak is far too strong, tastes like cold liquid toast!
A really good beer. Crisp, sharp taste, mild - moderate bitterness, alongside a decent amount of hops to make it a proper refreshing drink. Gold / light gold, floral with a decent head.

Dark beer full of cocoa, coffee and liquorice aroma and taste. Cream head, didnt seem to last. Good whole mouth feel with lasting memories of coffee and chocolate. Particularly hoppy. Good level of carbonation. Exceptionally good beer.
A good strong tasting beer. Good high level of hoppiness, along with grapefruit and citrus aroma and taste. Lasting creamy head, and golden colour.
A very refreshing beer, clear crisp and clean. Mild amount of citrus - more would be great! Light hoppiness, a better head would be good aswell.
A generally average beer. Nothing special about it, but does the job in an average pub!

Moderate slightly toasty aroma. Appearance moderate, nice ruby brown colour, no head at all. Taste again very much of toast, also with toffee and butterscotch. Overall, a pleasant beer, but cant quite get past the toast!
Light golden colour, not much of a head on it. Strong grapefruity / citrus aroma. Light hoppy taste.
Good ruby colour and strong lasting head. Strong pineapple and passion fruit aroma - quite refreshing. Taste more hoppy than fruity.
beer_name: Boxing Cat / The Celt Experience Cat Scratched Celt

review_blob: Pours golden / copper colour with s strong lasting head. Not too strong an aroma, but strong bitter hoppy taste. Fruity aftertaste. Very nice beer.
Relatively strong fruity aroma, but not as strong as other celt ales. Strong bitter taste, with a lasting citrus hops taste. Full mouth feel. Generally a refreshing ale without too much fuss.
heavy cloying sweetness, medium bitterness, golden, hazy, frothy, floral, hay, caramel, citrus,
beer_name: Ale Syndicate / Atlas / Celt Experience Seven Flowers
